  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, of course, there were some that were able to-- with enough money, to buy themself into an apartment that would be a little larger, so they were able to live a little more comfortable in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you were there with your mother and sister?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one of my grandmothers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's mother was with us in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I tell you, all these things happened so fast and-- and you are so emotionally involved that you don't even think, what do I think about the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No matter better what I thought about the ghetto, it didn't-- it didn't matter to anyone.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You just-- everyone was in there and everyone had to think about how you get a piece of bread to eat and how you're gonna get a job and how you're gonna exist.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it wasn't anything that I'm going to go in there and-- and evaluate whether I should or should not stay.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I couldn't get out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
